<BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Daimyo Wildfyre:<BR><STRONG>About the crit thing.<P>No, the individual hits are certainly not eye candy. I have crit'ed for 1301 with a 50/60 piercer. That's not a negligable amount of damage, by any means.<P>The point, however, si the frequency with which these hits occur. Assuming I have 255 DEX (buffed with shammy stuff and some DEX gear for the purposes of testing), I land a crit about every 30 normal strikes of a weapon. Percentage-wise, we're talking less than 5% of my total hits, and less than maybe 7% of my total damage comes from crits. THIS is why I call them eye candy--they make a big difference in single fights, but in the grand scheme of things they don't really add much to my damage during, say, a 5 hour period. Don't get me wrong, I LIKE crits. But they aren't anywhere near as powerful as lay hands or harm touch are, for example (of course, they shouldn't be--it's just a comparison).<P></STRONG><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Who told you that lie?  <P>Aren't as powerful?  Man, maybe your warrior has some bad luck with crits because my roomate crits a lot and very hard and if e turns that disc on, well...<P>Anyways, our LoH and HT can only be used once every 90 mins and will full heal a single target for roughly 3000k at the most on average when talking about max hp.<P>Your crits are terrible fierce and when you go beserk it gets worse and if you use the disc which recycles every 75 mins(decreases after a few levels) and allows you to do insane amounts of damage exceeding 3000k and you say LoH is better?  HT is better?  *LOL*<P>I'm sorry but I would trade my warrior in if this held true.<P>Even with my disc against undead I noticed that a warrior still out crit me on an UNDEAD mob.  My supposed specialty and he crit more than me with no disc and with my disc on.  <P>Every 30 swings you say?  More like every 22-25 but we'll say 30.  How long does it take for you to swing 30 times?  With haste?  With shissar? Wearing haste items?  Duel wielding?<P>Do you know what I do every 30 swings?  swing again, no matter what I fight.  Spells you say?  Clerics are always there so technically my usefullness there is neutralized.  What am I left with?  A weaker defense because the AC on my items being lower than a warriors and a mediocre fighting ability because my weaps are weaker and so am I.<P>Whoever you are basically saying that other classes have the same right to complain as us: <P>===>lake<P>  <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0">
