<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Usually Paladins are not NEEDED on raids but are always useful due to our tanking skills and our small little buffs such as divine glory and divine favour. As for paladins not being not as good of a tank as a warrior, your wrong to an extent. Warriors can take more damage than us yes, but we can heal ourselfs and also have LoH and DA. On raids damage dealing will always go to rogues(if they get some back), monks, and nukers. Warriors are just there to take damage and to taunt the mobs off of the damage dealers. As for nukes not landing on "uber" mobs, your wrong, on most parts. Just need a good ol' tash and malo and see the nukes fly. Yes some mobs are super MR and some only Lull line spells can hit but most uber mobs aren't like that. As for pets on raids, they are a no no on plane breaks and VS. As for most other boss mobs pets are always a good thing in taking and dealing some damage especially with a mage that has a epic chain summoning them. There are no raids that I have been on that NEED pets but i can think of at least 1 that would save your raid alot of trouble. Queen in chardok, has fire AE, on just about every chardok raid that I been on with my guild we had mages summon fire pets and just throwing them at her to ware(sp?) her down, then the melees run in and beat the crap outta her while the casters heal/debuff/nuke.<P>Laterz   <IMG SRC="cool.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>Daakkon Bladebane<BR>55 Knight<BR>King's Court<BR>Drinal
