<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Actually, warriors and rogues are usually the most damaging class on a raid. Monks can often compete with warriors; except the fact that fewer hp and the lack of lots of easy to acquire resist equipment means they die sooner.<P>On Velious mobs with hundreds of thousands of HP, no caster will outdamage a tank (any tank, includign all hybrids) with decent gear. A wizard who chain-nukes Velketor (HP circa 300k) will do perhaps 12-14000 damage with a full bar using the wrath of whatever (the unresistable giant one). A warrior in the typical raid situation deals somwhere around 25k damage, sometimes more or less depending on how many players are there.<P>"As for nukes not landing on "uber" mobs, your wrong, on most parts. Just need a good ol' tash and malo and see the nukes fly. "<BR>**Go land tashani or malosi on a Velious dragon. Then we'll talk. Obviously, if debuffs could land nukes could land. But most Velious mobs are so highly magic resistant that not even near-lure debuffs like the mage level 60 mala can land.**<P>"Yes some mobs are super MR and some only Lull line spells can hit but most uber mobs aren't like that. "<BR>**Trakanon, along with almost all Velious mobs are like that. The kunark and old-world dragons, as well as a number of the other kunark bosses are not, granted--but the toughest mobs in the game are.**<P>"As for paladins not being not as good of a tank as a warrior, your wrong to an extent. Warriors can take more damage than us yes, but we can heal ourselfs and also have LoH and DA."<BR>**Paladins are less capable main tanks after about level 40. They can still do it, granted, but more inefficiently due to lower AC and lower HP. Because clerics use CHeal at this point, the fewer the HP of the person being healed, the more inefficient it becomes. At 55, when warriors get Defensive, the ability for paladins to main tank relative to them becomes obsolete. However, paladins are superb secondary tanks in that they are excellent caster cover, stunner, and last-ditch lifesaver.**<P>And I agree completely--mage pets are extremely useful on the Queen in Chardok and also on the Queen in CoM. Almost essential.<P>--------------------<P>Do you know pain?<BR>Do you know rage?<BR>Do you know power?<P>Then that is all you need know of me.
