You need to define what kind of tank you're talking about. In a group without a strong healer, paladins are certainly more powerful than warriors. And they make good tanks up until the 50's. However, if a cleric is present to keep a warrior healthy, the warriro is simply a better tank than the paladin.<P>This doesn't really mean we're any "better" than paladins, just that we are more capable at doing one particular thing.<P>As far as Naggy raids go, it's been a long time since I went on one of those; however, back in the day ::grin:: the person who had the best fire resists was the last one to go. It all depends on a multitude of factors. Of course, if you're backing off to heal yourself against a dragon, you are soemtimes hurting the raid too--because the dragon isn't dropping as fast.<P>--------------------<P>Do you know pain?<BR>Do you know rage?<BR>Do you know power?<P>Then that is all you need know of me.
