52 mage here<P>pallies rule... i love pallies....<P>in a non raid scenario downtime=bad, unless we are taking massive reds down then its worth it but usually downtime is bad.  now a warrior is great, but then his downtime his just as great... unless we have a cleric... another xp sucking entity that keeps wars from being my favourite in groups.<P>i like hybrids, they are creative fun and hell smart enough to understand that mage groups are this odd thing to manage.  mind u i like clerics and i like chanters.  i just hate how dependant we have all become of them.  that puts the other good classes at a loss.   just the other day i had a baddass group of 2 rangers a rogue my mage self and 2 pallies.   guess who was tanking?  my pet !  they key to a good mage is not only crazy damage dealing but damage absorption by pets.  did u know if u stick a mob inside a pet or get the mage to put the pet inside the mob, the pet will take up all the aggro unless rEALLY pissed off?  yes it takes practice from the mage and the whole group but its a beautiful thing to see a coordinated group. (something hybrids and their multitalents are really good at )  u get a pally and ranger both on east and west, pet inside while i maneuver north and south, rogue whereever he needs to be.  tada.  massive death to all mobs with practically no downtime.  all classes can buff themselves and stay relatively full mana ready for the multi pulls that will inevitably arrive.  on 2 and 3 mob pulls is where each one shows their other talents... u cld split up each group pally ranger and me the other pally ranger and rogue for a 2 mob hit.  if a 3rd add comes i can hold him while they finish the other 2 off.   pallies are good tanks havent u heard  <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0">  then i can unload myh happlily full mana tank on one of their mobs to get it down fast.  a good mage can recast pets till there is no tomorrow so a mage pet can entertain a mob till needed or dead.<P>true efficiency is seen by organization and fast kills. oooh the war is so important because he can survive the 4 mob pull and tank till the chanter mezzes them all... um  why do that when  u can try to pull one by one.  of more than one comes then so be it but dont be so friggin eager to pull an army because it makes the war look cool.  then again for this to happen u need a chanter and cleric and war.  thats half a group just to make the tank look good.  i like hybrids because they milk the **** out of their abilities.  a good SK can outtaunt pretty much any mob off of a caster.  a good pally can tank everything for a few precious seconds everyone meds for that last bang spell.   when traveling pally root has saved me from imminent death.... ( yeah a pet less mage is a piece of ****... thus i hate raids that dont allow them... and most dont)  When ur out there in the field, the wilderness  u want these neat little abilities everyone whines that the clerics or warriors have better.   yes a clerics buffs overrides the pallies but u know they are not allways around.  clerics are great mind you.   they provide a safety net and allow for risky fun play..... at hte cost of xp.    ive had nice pally ranger rogue mage cleric warrior groups where the cleric just sits there to buff the melee chars.   just because a group has a war doesnt mean u have to use him as a meat shield.  u can fear, have pet tank,  dictate, stun silly  well u all know  what im talking about.   in the REAL EQ world, the one u are out there gaining xp, palladins rock.  versatility is key.  all classes are cool. and straying from the war cleric chanter combo can be a novel and gratifying experience.   <P>on raids:<P>do other hybrids help... yes<BR>are they needed....... no<BR>% of lifetime in raids............ very small<P>let the warriors have their fun... they are entitled to it.  we can have the rest of eq time  <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0"><P>those of you who keep trying to tell people that they are being stubborn and need to see the bic picture are all in the right.  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">  eq is not just about raids or just about xp.  its about traveling, exploring, testing, talking, treasure hunting, raiding, camping, factionbuilding, xp hunting and pvp fun.   most of the *****ing ive read in this article is "pallies suck, just look how everyone does this better and we arent wanted"  lol  any group wld take a pally over a mage post 50 any day.  u guys are needed to make rogues and rangers look good.  u guys keep parties alive thru root and blindness, loh, rezzes, heals, helming, waving that bright sword like a flag of triumph that lays waste to the vile hoards of underfoot.  ( sorry halflings hehe) did i forget to mention u do great role play?<P>quit ur *****ing folks.  u have it pretty good.  thank ur stars ur not one of the more hurting classes like wizards, mages, necros .... *gasp* look htey are all caster classes. <P>yea we all know that verant is trying to stick affirmative-classbalance-action upon us for being so powerful sub 50.   so i shut up and take it like a man. i play to have fun and i still have fun.  so relax folks and enjoy the fact you still have a very respected and utility high class that is the paladin. good luck guys and get those fiery defenders!!
